'From Squeak2.9alpha of 13 June 2000 [latest update: #2915] on 12 November 2000 at 5:55:56 pm'!"Change Set:		246LinkFixe-apbDate:			3 October 2000Author:			Andrew P BlackThe Link class method #nextLink:, which should answer a new instance of Link, instead answered nil.The fix is the obvious addition of 'yourself'.The one place that should have used this method -- SystemDictionary>>useUpMemory -- carefully programmed around this bug, so I changed that code so that it now uses #nextLink: in the natural way."!!Link class methodsFor: 'instance creation' stamp: 'apb 10/3/2000 15:55'!nextLink: aLink 	"Answer an instance of me referring to the argument, aLink."	^self new nextLink: aLink; yourself! !!SystemDictionary methodsFor: 'memory space' stamp: 'apb 10/3/2000 16:40'!useUpMemory	"For testing the low space handler..."	"Smalltalk installLowSpaceWatcher; useUpMemory"	| lst |	lst _ nil.	[true] whileTrue: [		lst _ Link nextLink: lst.	].! !